column17: 1.	We're trying to understand the composition of soils here better so that we can develop the best products and services for you and your land2.	To do this, we'd like to ask you some questions and also take ~200g of soil from either:        a) The maize field you harvested from last season (CONTROLS)   OR        b) The field you will use your OAF Maize inputs on for the long rains 2016 (OAF)3.	We'll analyze the soil to understand the nutrients it contains and its acidity.4.	We'll use this information to help make better recommendations and offer better products for you and farmers like you.5.	The survey will take approximately 30 minutes.6.	This is a multi-year study that will involve 1 visit from an M and E officer every August for the next 3-4 years to collect a soil sample from your field.7.	Participation in this study is completely voluntary and you may choose to decline participation in this study at any point in time.
